    "Name": "Stag",
    "Details": "The Stag was Clan Wolverine's redesign based on the Vulcan BattleMech. Khan Sarah McEvedy's orders led to the Stag, which transformed the venerable infantry-killer into a cavalry 'Mech that could also scout. As this design was pressed into service shortly after the conclusion of Operation KLONDIKE, it used Star League technology.<br>The Stag was built on an Endo Steel frame and powered by an XL engine. Ten tons of armor provided the 'Mech with the maximum possible protection. The Stag retained the Vulcan's top speed of 97 km/h, though it contained MASC that allowed the design to push up to 130 km/h in bursts. It was a bit less mobile, however, as it did not keep the jump jets.<br>The long-range threat from the cavalry Mech comes from one ER Large Laser. At close range it is supplemented by paired medium lasers and SRM-4s. Twelve double heat sinks handle all of the heat generated by the weapons.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
